-- Type synonymss for lazy texts
type LText = Data.Text.Lazy.Text
type LByteString = Data.ByteString.Lazy.ByteString

-- Exception handler with a more verbose name and smart constructor
type ExceptionHandler a = Control.Exception.Handler a

exHandler :: Exception e => (e -> IO a) -> ExceptionHandler a
exHandler = Control.Exception.Handler


infixl 1 &

(&) :: a -> (a -> b) -> b
x & f = f x

identity :: a -> a
identity x = x

map :: Functor f => (a -> b) -> f a -> f b
map = fmap

uncons :: [a] -> Maybe (a, [a])
uncons []     = Nothing
uncons (x:xs) = Just (x, xs)

applyN :: Int -> (a -> a) -> a -> a
applyN n f = X.foldr (.) identity (X.replicate n f)

print :: (X.MonadIO m, PBase.Show a) => a -> m ()
print = liftIO . PBase.print

show :: (Show a, ConvertibleStrings String b) => a -> b
show x = cs (PBase.show x)
{-# SPECIALIZE show :: Show  a => a -> String  #-}
{-# SPECIALIZE show :: Show  a => a -> Text  #-}
{-# SPECIALIZE show :: Show  a => a -> LText  #-}
